<subSubSection id="3F8B58C9FF885C68FF17125FFD653CC6" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="165" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="772E0B42FF885C6AFF17125FFC1D39D3" blockId="5.[136,1452,1094,2093]" box="[189,929,1130,1157]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFF17125FFEC739D3" bold="true" box="[189,379,1130,1156]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFE35125FFD2139D3" box="[415,669,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFE35125FFD2139D3" box="[415,669,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an accepted species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="772E0B42FF885C6AFF1712BBFDF538D7" blockId="5.[136,1452,1094,2093]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFF1712BBFE1739FF" bold="true" box="[189,427,1166,1192]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Nomenclature notes</emphasis>
:—As was the case with 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFD1712BAFCE939FF" box="[701,853,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beharensis">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFD1712BAFCE939FF" box="[701,853,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. beharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF885C6AFC0712BAFBF539FE" author="Hamet, R." box="[941,1097,1166,1193]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" pagination="109 - 111" refId="ref5772" refString="Hamet, R. (1906 [Janvier - Mars]) Note sur une nouvelle espece de Kalanchoe [Kalanchoe vantieghemii, as ' Van Tieghemi ']. Journal de Botanique [Morot] XX [20 e [annee] (No 1 - 3)]: 109 - 111. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 22106  page / 113 / mode / 1 up]" type="book chapter" year="1906">Hamet (1906)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed as 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFB5E12BAFA1939FF" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1906" box="[1268,1445,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vantieghemii">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFB5E12BAFA1939FF" box="[1268,1445,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. vantieghemii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in this instance, too, 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF885C6AFEC61286FDF2399B" author="Hamet, R." box="[364,590,1202,1229]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" pagination="138 - 139" refId="ref5901" refString="Hamet, R. (1907 b [Mars]) Note sur deux Kalanchoe malgaches. [Kalanchoe grandidieri Baill. and K. bonnieri Raym. - Hamet]. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France [Tome Cinquante-Quatrieme], Quatrieme serie - Tome VII, 54: 138 - 139. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 8676  page / 178 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1907">Hamet (1907b: 139)</bibRefCitation>
published a superfluous name when he published the name 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFB4D1286FADA399B" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1255,1382,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFB4D1286FADA399B" box="[1255,1382,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on exactly the same Grandidier [
<typeStatus id="A82AB5E0FF885C6AFE4712E3FD9E39A6" box="[493,546,1238,1265]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">type</typeStatus>
] material that Drake del Castillo used when he published the name 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFAAD12E2FA1839A7" box="[1287,1444,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFAAD12E2FA1839A7" box="[1287,1444,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hamet was seemingly aware of the publication of Drake del 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF885C6AFC8212CFFC6C3843" author="Castillo, E." box="[808,976,1274,1300]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" pagination="35 - 46" refId="ref5654" refString="Drake del Castillo, E. (1903) Note sur les plantes recueillies par M. Guillaume Grandidier dans le sud de Madagascar, en 1898 et 1901. (A suivre). Bulletin du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 9: 35 - 46. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 42893852  page / 45 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1903">Castillo (1903)</bibRefCitation>
and it is somewhat perplexing why Hamet redescribed Grandidier’s material that Drake del Castillo cited as “Cap Sainte-Marie (
<date id="032F2D82FF885C6AFBE1132BFB4F386F" box="[1099,1267,1310,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" value="1901-07-17">17 juillet 1901</date>
)” as 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFA86132AFA17386F" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1324,1451,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFA86132AFA17386F" box="[1324,1451,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). Note that 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFE3F1376FD8B380B" box="[405,567,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFE3F1376FD8B380B" box="[405,567,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Hamet only, not by “Hamet &amp; 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFB281377FB2A380B" box="[1154,1174,1346,1372]" country="Finland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15618" name="University of Helsinki" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Herbarium">H</collectionCode>
.Perrier” as recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF885C6AFF221353FDF938D7" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Allorge-Boiteau, L." box="[136,581,1382,1409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" refId="ref5454" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Allorge-Boiteau, L. (1995) Kalanchoe (Crassulacees) de Madagascar. Systematique, ecophysiologie et phytochimie. ICSN, CNRS, 91198 Gif-sur-Yvette, Editions Karthala, Paris, 252 pp." type="book" year="1995">Boiteau &amp; Allorge-Boiteau (1995: 149)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="772E0B42FF885C6AFF1713BEFAB33A2F" blockId="5.[136,1452,1094,2093]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF885C6AFF1713BEFE1138F3" author="Hamet, R." box="[189,429,1418,1445]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" pagination="138 - 139" refId="ref5901" refString="Hamet, R. (1907 b [Mars]) Note sur deux Kalanchoe malgaches. [Kalanchoe grandidieri Baill. and K. bonnieri Raym. - Hamet]. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France [Tome Cinquante-Quatrieme], Quatrieme serie - Tome VII, 54: 138 - 139. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 8676  page / 178 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1907">Hamet (1907b: 139)</bibRefCitation>
, when publishing the name 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFD5413BEFC3E38F3" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[766,898,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFD5413BEFC3E38F3" box="[766,898,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
stated: “Je vais maintenant décrire une espèce nouvelle, voisine du 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFEC4139BFDC8389F" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1888" box="[366,628,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandidieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFEC4139BFDC8389F" box="[366,628,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe Grandidieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
par l’ensemble de ses caractères floraux, mais très nettement différente de celui-ci par ses feuilles cylindriques, en forme de stylet, non planes obovées, par ses fleurs disposées en cyme bipare, non en petits groupes de 3 (ou rarement 2) disposés le long d’une hampe allongée. Cette espèce se distingue encore du 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFF04102FFE9B3B63" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[174,295,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFF04102FFE9B3B63" box="[174,295,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
précité par sa corolle plus large et moins longue, de couleur rouge sang, non mauve-violette, et par ses carpelles beaucoup moins allongés. Par ses feuilles elle se rapproche du 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFC48100BFA963B0F" authority="Deflers" authorityName="Deflers" box="[994,1322,1598,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="teretifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFC48100BFB6C3B0F" box="[994,1232,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe teretifolia</emphasis>
Deflers
</taxonomicName>
<superScript id="80E4A60AFF885C6AFA80100BFA8E3B1B" attach="left" box="[1322,1330,1598,1612]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">1</superScript>
, d’Arabie, dont elle diffère par l’ensemble de ses caractères floraux. J’en ferai le 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFC051057FB243B2B" authority="Bonnieri." authorityName="Bonnieri." box="[943,1176,1634,1660]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFC051057FB2F3B2B" box="[943,1171,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe Bonnieri</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
” [English: “ 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFA801057FA883B2B" box="[1322,1332,1634,1660]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
shall now describe a new species, which is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFDC010B3FCD73BF7" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1888" box="[618,875,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandidieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFDC010B3FCD73BF7" box="[618,875,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe grandidieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in all its floral characters, but very clearly different from it by its cylindrical, styletiform, non-obovate leaves, and by its flowers arranged in a biparous cyme, not in small groups of three (or rarely two) arranged along an elongated stalk. This species is further distinguished from the aforementioned 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFEEA10C7FE053A5B" box="[320,441,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFEEA10C7FE053A5B" box="[320,441,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFE6110C6FDD23A5B" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1888" box="[459,622,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandidieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFE6110C6FDD23A5B" box="[459,622,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. grandidieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] by its larger and shorter, blood red, not purple-violet corolla, and by its much less elongated carpels. In its leaves it is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFCB91123FBE13A67" authority="Deflers" authorityName="Deflers" box="[787,1117,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="teretifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFCB91123FBBE3A67" box="[787,1026,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe teretifolia</emphasis>
Deflers
</taxonomicName>
<superScript id="80E4A60AFF885C6AFBF71123FBD93A73" attach="left" box="[1117,1125,1814,1828]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">1</superScript>
, from Arabia, from which it differs in all its floral characters. 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFE5C110EFE433A02" box="[502,511,1851,1877]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
shall name it 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFD33110FFCC03A02" authority="bonnieri." authorityName="Bonnieri." box="[665,892,1850,1877]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFD33110FFCCB3A03" box="[665,887,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe bonnieri</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
”] Superscript 1 refers to: “1. 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFB69110FFB663A03" box="[1219,1242,1850,1876]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
. DEFLERS, 
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFAE7110EFD173A2F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
Note sur un 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFF01116BFD833A2F" authority="de l'Arabie" authorityName="de l'Arabie" box="[171,575,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remarquable">Kalanchoe remarquable de l’Arabie</taxonomicName>
tropicale
</emphasis>
, Bull. Soc. bot. Fr., XL, pp. 298–301, Pl. IIl– 
<date id="032F2D82FF885C6AFB02116BFABC3A2F" box="[1192,1280,1886,1912]" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" value="1893-05">
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFB02116BFB003A2F" box="[1192,1212,1886,1912]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
1893
</date>
.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="772E0B42FF885C69FF1711B6FC1D3C8E" blockId="5.[136,1452,1094,2093]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,473]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="164" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">
However, shortly after having described 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFD2F11B6FCB83ACB" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[645,772,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFD2F11B6FCB83ACB" box="[645,772,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and while working on his monograph of 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFB7011B7FEAB3A97" authority=", Hamet (1907 a: 887)" authorityName="Hamet" authorityPageNumber="887" authorityYear="1907" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFB7011B7FAEF3ACB" box="[1242,1363,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF885C6AFACB11B6FEAB3A97" author="Hamet, R." pageId="5" pageNumber="163" pagination="869 - 900" refId="ref5850" refString="Hamet, R. (1907 a) Monographie du genre Kalanchoe. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2, 7: 869 - 900. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 105267  page / 939 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1907">Hamet (1907a: 887)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
noted: “Observation: 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFDA61192FD943A96" box="[524,552,1959,1985]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
. Drake del Castillo a, dans sa description, donné les feuilles comme linéaires. Me basant sur la forme des cicatrices laissées sur la tige par les feuilles tombées, je les avais décrites comme cylindriques, stylettiformes. L’échantillon rapporté dans l’alcool par 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF885C6AFD5F11DAFCAD355E" box="[757,785,2031,2057]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
. Geay et dont les feuilles ont conservé leur forme naturelle m’a donné raison. La description du 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF885C6AFDB71E26FD06357B" box="[541,698,2066,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="5" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF885C6AFDB71E26FD06357B" box="[541,698,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="163">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n’est mentionnée dans aucun recueil bibliographique. L’échantillon authentique, conservé dans l’herbier Drake del Castillo, ne porte aucune mention qui fasse supposer qu’il ait été décrit. Aussi croyant avoir à faire á une espèce nouvelle, je lui avais donné le nom de 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8B5C69FBA316F6FB303D8B" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1033,1164,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8B5C69FBA316F6FB303D8B" box="[1033,1164,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">K. Bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Un hasard m’apprit trop tard que ce nom faisait double emploi.” [English: “Observation: Mr. Drake del Castillo, in his description, gave the leaves as linear. Based on the shape of the scars left on the stem by the fallen leaves, 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF8B5C69FBE0173EFBEF3C72" box="[1098,1107,267,293]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
described them as cylindrical, styletiform. The specimen brought back in alcohol by Mr [Martin François] Geay [1859–1910], the leaves of which retained their natural form, proved me right. The description of 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8B5C69FCF11766FC473C3B" box="[859,1019,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8B5C69FCF11766FC473C3B" box="[859,1019,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not mentioned in any bibliographic record. The authentic specimen, kept in the Drake del Castillo herbarium, bears no mention to suggest that it had been described. Also, believing 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF8B5C69FE1A17AEFE053CE2" box="[432,441,411,437]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
had to do with a new species, 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF8B5C69FCA617AEFCA93CE2" box="[780,789,411,437]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
gave it the name of 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8B5C69FC5D17AEFBCA3CE3" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1907" box="[1015,1142,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bonnieri">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8B5C69FC5D17AEFBCA3CE3" box="[1015,1142,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">K. bonnieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectionCode id="11809387FF8B5C69FB2917AEFB303CE2" box="[1155,1164,411,437]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
only fortuitously realised too late that the name was a duplicate [a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8B5C69FD76178AFCC73C8F" box="[732,891,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8B5C69FD76178AFCC73C8F" box="[732,891,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]”.]
</paragraph>
<caption id="23EE5BCAFF8B5C69FF221E25FB1D3571" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571445" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6571445" box="[136,1185,2064,2086]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" startId="6.[136,229,2064,2086]" targetBox="[226,1361,497,2039]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="772E0B42FF8B5C69FF221E25FB1D3571" blockId="6.[136,1185,2064,2086]" box="[136,1185,2064,2086]" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8B5C69FF221E25FF423572" bold="true" box="[136,254,2064,2086]" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8B5C69FEA91E25FE613572" box="[259,477,2064,2085]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8B5C69FEA91E25FE613572" box="[259,477,2064,2085]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="164">Kalanchoe linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a red-flowered, lianoid-shrubby species. Photograph: Gideon F. Smith.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="772E0B42FF8A5C68FF1716ABFD653CC6" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="165">
The type of the name 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8A5C68FE0616AAFDF53DEF" box="[428,585,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8A5C68FE0616AAFDF53DEF" box="[428,585,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="165">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of a single specimen. The collector of the specimen is “ 
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8A5C68FAA616AAFF143D8B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="165">
<collectionCode id="11809387FF8A5C68FAA616AAFA9F3DEE" box="[1292,1315,159,185]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
. Grandidier s.n
</emphasis>
.” and the date is 
<date id="032F2D82FF8A5C68FECD16F7FE453D8B" box="[359,505,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" value="1901-07-17">17 July 1901</date>
. As this is the only Grandidier specimen we could trace with this date and locality we conclude that this specimen constitutes the 
<typeStatus id="A82AB5E0FF8A5C68FDDB16D3FD6F3C57" box="[625,723,230,256]" pageId="7" pageNumber="165">holotype</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="B09170C1FF8A5C68FCC216D2FBBB3C57" box="[872,1031,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8A5C68FCC216D2FBBB3C57" box="[872,1031,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="165">K. linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it is the “ 
<specimenCount id="6197C0CBFF8A5C68FB3016D3FA863C57" box="[1178,1338,230,256]" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF8A5C68FAF816D3FEB43C73" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." pageId="7" pageNumber="165" refId="ref6952" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. [Regnum Vegetabile 159], 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="45E5D750FF8A5C68FF22173EFF003C73" box="[136,188,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="165">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 9.1) indicated [or used] by Drake del 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF8A5C68FD55173FFC6B3C73" author="Castillo, E." box="[767,983,266,292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" pagination="35 - 46" refId="ref5654" refString="Drake del Castillo, E. (1903) Note sur les plantes recueillies par M. Guillaume Grandidier dans le sud de Madagascar, en 1898 et 1901. (A suivre). Bulletin du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 9: 35 - 46. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 42893852  page / 45 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1903">Castillo (1903: 41)</bibRefCitation>
when he published the name. This view coincides with that of 
<bibRefCitation id="130076B3FF8A5C68FED1171BFC923C1F" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Allorge-Boiteau, L." box="[379,814,302,329]" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" refId="ref5454" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Allorge-Boiteau, L. (1995) Kalanchoe (Crassulacees) de Madagascar. Systematique, ecophysiologie et phytochimie. ICSN, CNRS, 91198 Gif-sur-Yvette, Editions Karthala, Paris, 252 pp." type="book" year="1995">Boiteau &amp; Allorge-Boiteau (1995: 149)</bibRefCitation>
who state that the “Holo- [
<collectionCode id="11809387FF8A5C68FBFE171BFBDB3C1E" box="[1108,1127,302,329]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="7" pageNumber="165" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
